I'll disagree. While the general ideas normally involved with FT often lead to the ripping of ideas from pop culture, its easy to put your own spin on it, and even then, you can still make new, fascinating stuff. Plus, it gives you a chance to run any nation style you want without constraint, even stuff that doesn't already exist. No need to examine history and geography and culture and religion, just do something!

I also don't see a lot of reason to stick to MT. Its the conservative way to RP, since it is in modern technology and times, and while that means it's safe, its been done far more across not just NS, but elsewhere. Sure, its easy too, but being able to wield technologies that some may have their heads spinning over is a lot more fun.

As for other tech levels, I think past tech is also an interesting idea... if its not within the last 122-ish years. Late 19th century is a bit iffy as well, but anything earlier than that and its cool. I'd actually like to see, maybe, some nations based on societies from BCE times.

Of course, I say this as an FT player myself, so obviously I'll side with what I have.
